The paper discusses enhancements to Answer Set Programming (ASP) with theory reasoning capabilities, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The focus of the paper is on linear constraints, which are commonly used in Logic and Verification (cs.LO) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also presents empirical evaluations, which could fall under Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Data Management (cs.DM).
